ED_Title: Election of the Vice-Presidents of the General Assembly at its seventy-eighth session
ED_DecisionText: At its 74th plenary meeting, on 1 June 2023, the General Assembly, in accordance with rule 30 of the rules of procedure of the Assembly and paragraphs 2 and 3 of the annex to resolution 33/138 of 19 December 1978, elected the following 21 Member States as Vice-Presidents of the General Assembly at its seventy-eighth session: BOLIVIA (PLURINATIONAL STATE OF), CHINA, CONGO, ESTONIA, FRANCE, GAMBIA, ICELAND, IRAN (ISLAMIC REPUBLIC OF), MALAYSIA, MOROCCO, NETHERLANDS (KINGDOM OF THE), RUSSIAN FEDERATION, SENEGAL, SINGAPORE, SRI LANKA, SURINAME, UGANDA, UNITED KINGDOM OF GREAT BRITAIN AND NORTHERN IRELAND, UNITED STATES OF AMERICA, UZBEKISTAN and ZAMBIA.
ED_Disclaimer: The final text of this decision will be contained in document A/77/49 (Vol. III) after editorial review.
